name: HashData
description: The HashData class describes different types of hashes on a given object (e.g., file, part of a file, email).

HashTargetID.name: HashTargetID
HashTargetID.description: An identifier that references a subset of the object being hashed.  The semantics of this identifier are specified by the scope attribute.

Hash.name: Hash
Hash.description: The hash of an object.  See Section 3.26.1.

FuzzyHash.name: FuzzyHash
FuzzyHash.description: The fuzzy hash of an object.  See Section 3.26.2.

scope.name: scope
scope.description: A means by which to extend the scope attribute.  See Section 5.1.1.
